criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age 18-75 years;

          -  confirmed cirrhosis based on liver biopsy or clinical findings;

          -  without decompensated events (e.g. ascites, bleeding, or overt encephalopathy);

          -  scheduled to undergo esophagogastroduodenoscopy, spleen stiffness measurement and
             liver stiffness measurement;

          -  estimated survival time>24 months, and model for end-stage liver disease score<19, and
             without liver transplant;

          -  with written informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  contradictions for esophagogastroduodenoscopy;

          -  accepted primary prevention (non-selective beta blockers or endoscopic variceal
             ligation);

          -  time frame between elastography measurement and esophagogastroduodenoscopy>14 days;

          -  diagnosed as hepatocellular carcinoma;

          -  absence of spleen or splenectomy.
